            <title>[OAK-2716] Background operation lock not released when DocumentNodeStore is closed</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/OAK-2716</link>
                <project id="12313221" key="OAK">Jackrabbit Oak</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/OAK-2642&quot; title=&quot;DocumentNodeStore.dispose() may leave repository in an inconsistent state&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;OAK-2642&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;OAK-2642&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; introduced a check in DocumentNodeStore before a commit is created. The call will fail if the store is closed. The new check does not release the background read lock when it throws an exception. This may block a concurrent dispose call performing a shutdown of the repository.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
